  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. The key elements usually include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration: Making the funds appear legal and usable\n\nSpecific details can vary by jurisdiction, but most legal systems criminalize intentional efforts to hide the origins of money from illegal activities.",
